item.description:
@Epic_Steve wrote:

[quote=“supernovarsps, post:2, topic:353877”]i get this error

src\server\model\players\PlayerSave.java:119: 'else' without 'if' else if (token.equals("TOKEN")) { ^ 1 error Press any key to continue . . . [/quote]
You have an else, without an if. Example,

public class ExampleClass {
    public void elseWithoutIf() {
         // BAD CODE - ERROR
         else if(1 = 2)
         {
             /*
                  This section of code is wrong. Notice that you have an else statement without an if statement.
             */
         }

        // GOOD CODE - NO ERROR
        /* This second section of code is fine. You have the else if statement following an if statement.*/
        if(1 = 2) {
        
       } else if(1 = 1) {
       
       }
    }
}
